50|$|Systemic oppression has {{an effect}} on {{violence}} experienced by <b>black</b> <b>women.</b> When reported, <b>Black</b> <b>women</b> receive the least amount of aid and protection from local, state, and federal laws. A reason for lack of protection from the government is the ongoing stereotypes which imagine <b>Black</b> <b>women</b> <b>to</b> be vulgar and violent beings. This permeated ideology causes instances of abuse and violence experienced by <b>black</b> <b>women</b> <b>to</b> go unreported and/or underreported.|$|R
