50|$|Sistas Organizing to Survive (SOS) is a {{grassroots}} mobilization of <b>black</b> <b>women</b> {{in the fight}} against HIV/AIDS. Launched on June 20, 2008, the movement aims to mobilize and empower <b>black</b> <b>women</b> <b>to</b> stop the spread of HIV/AIDS. The goal is <b>to</b> test 100,000 <b>black</b> <b>women</b> by 2010. <b>To</b> date, eight local SOS conferences have been conducted, more than 4,000 people have taken the online pledge, and 88,000-plus <b>black</b> <b>women</b> have been tested.|$|R
